        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 9:00AM EDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 900 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Stockland, or 7 miles southeast of Milford, moving southeast at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dunnington, Ambia, Otterbein, Templeton, Boswell, and Oxford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
